dle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Chetwode","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Chetwood  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Chatwood","meanings":["English:  see  Chetwood  ."]},{"name":"Chetwood","meanings":["English: habitational name from Chetwode in Buckinghamshire or from Cheetwood in Cheetham, Manchester (Lancashire). This placename consists of the Brittonic placename element <i>cēto-</i> ‘wood’, with an explanatory addition in Old English of <i>wudu</i> ‘wood’. The surname may also be a Shropshire variant of   Chatwin  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert De Chetwode was born in 1171, in England, his father, Ralph Chetwood, was 26 and his mother, MRS Ralph Chetwood, was 23. He married Sybil Strange de Fredville in 1197, in Wolston, Warwickshire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1205, in Chetwode, Buckinghamshire, England, at the age of 34."},"et":{"1171–1204/1205":"1171–1205","1171–1205":"1171–1205","1174–1200":"1174–1200","1197–Male":"1197–Surnud","1198–Male":"1198–Surnud","1145–Male":"1145–Surnud","1149–Female":"1149–Surnud","1205":"1205","1149":"1149","1200":"1200","1145":"1145","1204/1205":"1205","1198":"1198","1197":"1197","1174":"1174","about 1179":"umbes 1179","about 1198":"umbes 1198","1171":"1171","about 1197":"umbes 1197","Wolston, Warwickshire, England":"Wolston, Warwickshire, England","Chetwode, Buckinghamshire, England":"Chetwode, Buckinghamshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1171–1204/1205":"1171–1205","1171–1205":"1171–1205","1174–1200":"1174–1200","1197–Male":"1197–Kuollut","1198–Male":"1198–Kuollut","1145–Male":"1145–Kuollut","1149–Female":"1149–Kuollut","1205":"1205","1149":"1149","1200":"1200","1145":"1145","1204/1205":"1205","1198":"1198","1197":"1197","1174":"1174","about 1179":"noin 1179","about 1198":"noin 1198","1171":"1171","about 1197":"noin 1197","Wolston, Warwickshire, England":"Wolston, Warwickshire, England","Chetwode, Buckinghamshire, England":"Chetwode, Buckinghamshire, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"1171–1204/1205":"1171–1205","1171–1205":"1171–1205","1174–1200":"1174–1200","1197–Male":"1197–Décédé","1198–Male":"1198–Décédé","1145–Male":"1145–Décédé","1149–Female":"1149–Décédée","1205":"1205","1149":"1149","1200":"1200","1145":"1145","1204/1205":"1205","1198":"1198","1197":"1197","1174":"1174","about 1179":"environ 1179","about 1198":"environ 1198","1171":"1171","about 1197":"environ 1197","Wolston, Warwickshire, England":"Wolston, Warwickshire, Angleterre","Chetwode, Buckinghamshire, England":"Chetwode, Buckinghamshire, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Robert De Chetwode est né en 1171, à Angleterre, son père, Ralph Chetwood, avait 26 ans et sa mère, MRS Ralph Chetwood, avait 23 ans. Il a épousé Sybil Strange de Fredville en 1197, à Wolston, Warwickshire, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au mo